    {
      "id": "theme-state-grammar-overview",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Theme State Grammar",
      "position": {
        "x": -120,
        "y": -140
      },
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "width": 520,
      "height": 260,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Theme State Grammar\n\nPort design exposed a larger issue: the app needs a more intentional state grammar.\n\nThe question is not just what color ports should be.\nIt is what the app allows to be loud, what stays calm, and how interactive states are expressed consistently.",
