    {
      "id": "theme-state-grammar-states",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Candidate State Vocabulary",
      "position": {
        "x": 940,
        "y": 120
      },
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "width": 420,
      "height": 300,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Candidate State Vocabulary\n\n- `calm` / default\n- `hover`\n- `active`\n- `drag-target`\n- `connected`\n- `focused`\n- `disabled`\n- `warning` / `error`\n\nThe goal is not maximal taxonomy. The goal is enough shared language that components stop making up their own emphasis rules.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
